name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Lovely place to visit and bike. There are BBQ pits near by. Good place to sit and enjoy fresh air. The children's playground is small.
You can swim if you want. You can see airplanes landing every 5 minutes.  Washrooms are not clean enough üòï

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Wanted to explore a new waterfront with the family today, so we decided to visit the Changi Beach Park. We didn't like it because it's quite a small park with narrower pathways, lots of trash, and lots of visitors doing things that were opposite of the guidelines on the signs. For example, right in front of the "Do not feed the birds" sign, there was a group of people feeding the birds. Nobody cared about the No Smoking signs there either. There's a sign that says you can't pitch tents there, but there are tents galore, and almost all of the sheltered areas were taken over by people who look like they set up dwelling there with stoves, pots and pans, cleaning equipment, clothes lines, etc. Hopefully, the authorities will clean up the area soon because it does seem almost like a homeless slum there.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Standard beach experience in a Singapore with the below exceptions
A. You can see planes take off every few minutes. So if you are into that you can come.
B. Has a good halal seafood/ food options nearby.
C. Found a lot of dead fishes on the beach.
D. More birds than usual.

Might be a good place to end the day if you are already in the area, otherwise find the beach nearest to your place.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Took my paddle board out to the beach on a weekday during high tide. Was happy that it was not crowded. The beach was quite nice although it could be cleaner. Had a nice time. Managed to wash up in the public shower place before my lunch at a Alfresco restaurant (Sea Grill) by the beach.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: A great place to spend peaceful time with your family and friends. Kids can enjoy on the beach while you can relax.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: If u wanna see the planes landing at the nearby Changi Airport then tis is the place to come. Standing on the familiar concret bridge u can hv a good view of the planes at very low altitude. Changi jetty is nearby & u can take a bumboat to Pulau Ubin. There r many eateries around this place & oso a hawker centre which sells good beef horfun, ipoh horfun, nasi lemak & goreng pisang! On weekends there r many bikers cycling from all the nearby park connectors to enjoy the beautiful beach & foods.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: A good site for picnics, windy and scenic. A long stretch of breakwaters to relax on, while watching the waves hit against the rocks. A good place for aeroplanes spotting, as you can see them coming from afar, approaching slowly over the sea towards inland and fly right above your heads. Fantastic view of planes for aviation enthusiasts.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: The beach is best suited for people who are tired of East Coast and Sentosa. The beach is near to good food and the newly opened PCN Changi Bay Point. Popular for both picnic goers and bikers

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Beautifully made park that provides a different vantage point of SG besides West Coast Park and Eaat Coast Park. Similar facilities are available at the park from GoCycling (rental bicycles), toilets and park canopy shelter during rainy days.

Majority of people cycle through this place and its recommended to bring your bicycles to cycle as a group.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Definitely not one of the best beaches Singapore has to visit but it still has its charms. Photographers will love that this is the beach to be at to capture planes landing as they come in from the NNE direction. There are quite a number of people camping/living at the shelter areas.
Ample parking spaces at the many car parks.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: A beautiful park with plenty of shade and cooling sea breeze. Amenities like Changi Village Hawker Centre, clean toilets are a short walk away. The ferry to Pulau Ubin is nearby.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Wonderful area right on the beach. Parking can be difficult on the weekends. Mostly empty during weekdays. There are bike rental and drinking places. Can see various islands, ships of all kinds and Johor.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Nice place to chill after run. Also cycled, so always find this place a good stop-over for quick bite at Changi Village Hawker Centre before continuing our ride towards MBS (via TMCR/ ECP)üëç!  But do note that weekends will be packedüòú.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: The best beach if you really want to go chill, sit by the sea and watch the passing ships and the landing planes roar above you!! Changi Beach just has a different vibe to it!! :)

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Lovely weather. Promo on rental of family bike. Clean toilet but shower head n toilet door slightly faulty. also there's difficulty to wash of sand from clothes. Ive to squat and bend down n hurt my back aft 5 mins of doing so. Haha

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: A long route that leads to the newly opened Changi Bay Point, the scenery may be lacking but there's a good cycling path. Along the way you'll see Changi Village and SAF Ferry Terminal too.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: What a pleasant place to hand with ur family. You will find clean and neat beach after ECP in Singapore , cloture to this you have lot of eateries, And an Indian hindu temple with biggest lord hanuman statue. Great location to visit for weekends eve

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: After a 2 years never visit changi beach park..still looks cool interesting,fun and so much more things to do with family and friends to just spend time with or  make memories to look back one day..

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Limited parking lot.
Alot of camping.  And every minute you can enjoy seeing plane landing üòä

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Day out at Changi Village - surprises from the ocean. Did not expect to catch an octopus! Just chilling here in the evening and enjoying the sea breeze is a joy in itself!

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: If you wana spend quality afternoon, Changi park is the right place to visit. Withness gorgeous sunset and numerous flights descending at Changi airport

name: Changi Beach Park

name: Changi Beach Park

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: The beach is rough, full of stones and other trash. Some BBQ pit near by, but closed for safety. The children playground is small. Not particularly fun place. Can see planes landing...

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Excellent beach to watch planes about to land in Changi airport. Very relaxed and serene surroundings. Great for BBQ and beach play.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Lovely place to bike for sure. I rode all the way from Area B bike shop - east coast park till changi beach park. 58 km round trip. Took 2 hour plus to complete each side

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Close watching flights  arriving to changi airport. Not too crowded as compared to east coast park

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: I love the place. The BBQ pits can be booked in advance and the entire atmosphere is energetic and the view is impeccable

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: The park is usually packed with people on weekends. There are facilities like toilet and eating place. The link to the Changi Bay Point is the new addition within the vicinity.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Lovely place to go to if you want to get away from the hustle and  bustle. It's more out of the way compared to East Coast Park, so definitely lesser crowd. It my favorite cycling place when ECP gets a bit crowded.

Of course not forgetting that Changi Hawker Centre and its Nasi Lemak is just around the corner.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: A beautiful place to unwind and enjoy the sea breeze. There are children playground and bicycle trails.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Hawker reopened üòä Can see v much the Oriental pied hornbills in the trees.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Not too many people. Can see planes and ships passing by. Swim and play sandcastle at the beach. Many cycling and fishing enthusiasts. Eat or tapao first at nearby Changi Hawker Centre.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Nice park with beach view and flight landing also

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Low tides are one of the best at changi beach. When you are visiting do watch out your steps while walking on the beach bed. Also do not pick any marine life.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Serene place peaceful. Tho wish their toilets could be more cleaner

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: A quiet and peaceful beach where one can see planes just taking off into the air.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Amazing place.
Well connected by cycling track.
Superb place to enjoy sunset with family and friends.
People can enjoy, fishing and even do dry picnic.
It is best to visit in morning and evening.

Be mindful of social gathering restrictions due to COVID.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Great place to have short cycling experience..Able to rent bike for two for $40 for 2hours use

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Nice calm and quiet place. Nice place to do picnic and spend time with family. Facilities are there for playing in beach if needed. Also facilitates for grill and barbeque etc .. if you are an plane enthusiastic then definitely a place for you to visit

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Nice place to spend some weekend for picnic or cycling. Eating place is nearby. Toilet is clean as they have been renovated

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Nice beach park with banks, pavilion, grill places, restrooms, children‚Äòs playground and various parking lots. It is a pity that some people left their garbage on the beach even though there are garbage bins everywhere. That‚Äôs why we saw at least 6 rats running around the pave way.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: the place is cool and comfortable to relax and have fun it's a good place I like to play here

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Come with a partner and enjoy a nice picnic here. It is not very large beach. There is an airport nearby so you can click pics with the planes flying at a very low altitude from here.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Good place to hangout and enjoy fresh air at the same time. Places maybe crowded during weekends or holidays, but it's still spacious for people to walk even when crowded.

You can jog or cycle here too! Also, the place is pet friendly üòâ

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Great vibes~ view not blocked by ships like at ECP. Can see Tekong!

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: A good place for plane watching and also picnic with family. Located near the airport. You can see planes take off and land. Nearby good food places too!

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Out on a late weekday morning, along the peaceful stretch of Changi Beach Park. Not crowded, with a few families enjoying the beach.

Spotted a Hornbill in the tree, saw 2 otters swimming in the channel.. wow what a day!

Learnt the neighboring island was part of British defense outpost and the site of the changi beach massacre during the Japanese Occupation.. this place is rich in history, yet there is calmness.

Cross the pedestrian bridge to get to changi village and have your nasi lemak! Or to continue onto the coastal walk on the opposite bank. Have a chat with the fishermen on their catch. Just chill‚Ä¶

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Long stretch of sand beach. Despite many people it‚Äôs relatively easy to find spot with safe distancing from others. Bring a deck chair and a drink, great way to relax and enjoy the sea view in the evening.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Nice calm beach away from the usual crowd in ECP. Easy access by public  transport.A perfect spot to watch the sunset.Can have a fun picnic ,ride a bike from the rental shop nearby. An array of restaurants.  A good place for fishing.
Gave a 4 rating as sometimes the shoreline is trashed with fishlines fishhooks and seaweeds.

name: Changi Beach Park

A relaxing park located at the far east of Singapore. Enjoy the scenary, village lifestyle by seeing the old fishing boat ferrying passenger..

Prominent statue of the Inscription of the island. Is good place for a picnic with family and kids. Must have a car to reach changi village and walking distance to park.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: When have light rain so nice to see..

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Fresh air , green, running ,sea sight and BBQ also can do. Love this place but noising (flight up to down every 3-5 minutes ).

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Windy area, good for fishing and picnics as it‚Äôs calm and relaxing here (apart from the plane sounds!). Really recommend people to visit this place for a walk or cycling or just hanging out

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Nice place to hang out when the weather is nice. A good crowd was there engaged in various activities but not too crowded to feel like its cramped. Very relaxing. Theres a big hawker center right beside the park which is a plus if grabbing a bite is on the agenda.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Beautiful spot to relax, swim, and be active. There is a hawker center nearby and the boats to Palau Ubin. This makes for a great full day of thigs to do and places to go in the east of Singapore!

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: It is a beautiful quiet place and many camping Site if you want to stay over night, but have to remember to register in advance for your campaign

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
One of the less crowded beaches in Singapore. Lovely place to soak in the water and watch the planes take off/land just above your head.

Can get crowded, so go early (before 10 am on weekends) to get a good spot under a shady tree.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: It's breezy & beautiful beach to stroll, bike, play, picnic, etc. Relatively different from East Coast beach, Changi beach is so laid back. There are a lot seagulls flying & gliding on the sky, flock of pigeons, nice large green field, palm trees, trees, a cafe in the park. You can see some boats & their activities at the jetty too. And it's pretty near Changi Village for those who love to explore some culiners

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
One of a few beach in Singapore that you do not need to see 'parked' ships and tankers.
A lot of people fishing and camping in the beach but you can still capture the serenity of the sea.
A popular place for runners and cyclists too.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Nice and quiet beach park for people who likes to take a stroll or have a picnic. There are playgrounds and fitness corner. Overall  really nice ambience as the view is overlooking other nearby small island and not clustered with large cargo ships. It's just right  beside Changi Village Hawker which has lots of food options.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Beautiful Beach on reclaimed land. Waves and flights compete to sound louder.

Take your cycle and do a round up of this serine place.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Best place for Walk, Run or bike riding for family. the park is awesome and evening visit is the best either nice breeze or watch flights landing/takeoffs

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Spring tide on the dawn of 26/6/21 drew me to visit the intertidal zone of Changi Beach which I have heard much about but have not personally witnessed. It was an eye opener for me to spot the rich diversity of marine animals nestled among the seagrass exposed within the brief window period of a low tide. One can only imagine an even richer diversity of marine life deeper into the sea. I was grateful to meet a man named Mr Kiew, who is a nature volunteer with NParks and provides educational information to the public on the marine creatures they have spotted. For me it was a fascinating experience when I tilted a sea shell to a side and out emerged the beautiful claws and legs of an orange striped hermit crab which then tried to return its borrowed home to an upright state. Nature‚Äôs creation is awesome, with every living creature having a purpose in their existence, and there‚Äôs so much to appreciate that all of us co-exists on the same planet.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Great park by the sea. One gets nice breeze even on a hottest day. For best experience visit after 5 pm though. A lot to see and do. Can get busy on the weekend.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Changi Beach Park is a place I truly enjoy visiting. The sea breeze is absolutely windy and strong. The place is very clean as well. It's a great place for families and friends to come for outdoor activities.

You can bring along your own food, tables and chairs to have a picnic. Some of them also bought speakers to play their music while enjoying quality time with each other.

There are many empty spaces for people to play frisbee and ball games.

The sand it has allows children to build sand castles. Children can also rent bicycles, roller skates to play in the park. There is also playground for kids and adults to enjoy.

Couples also come here to take their wedding photos.

Some come here to swim in the sea.

There are also very good food in Changi Village which allows people to have a good meal after enjoying the meal.

Beside Changi Beach, there's also a ferry terminal where you can see ferry passing by. As it's also near Changi airport, you also get to see airplanes flying pass once in a while.

#ILoveChangiBeachPark

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: A family-friendly beach and park. One of the best beaches in SG as it looks cleaner than ECP and Pasir Ris Park beach and less ships in the horizon. The restaurant at the entrance ‚Äî The Seagrill serves luscious food and drinks, the Cheval‚Äôs Singapore Sling cocktail is a must try!

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Clear, windy , clean beach.
Can swim, water sports, fishing, gathering, family bonding n sand castle building.

Just seconds to the carpark.
Convenience n close to the famous Changi point food court.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Although it may seem inaccessible, there are actually a few buses that get there quite easily. A nice place to chill with the family to enjoy the sea, wind and nature. The fact that it's really close to Changi Village is also a plus point.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Nice location but so many people camping, fishing, cycling here. There were a lot of trash in the resting area. People can u help to keep the environment clean as u enjoyed the view?

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: One of our favourite Sunday walk Park where one can see beautiful sunrise, sea breeze n view of ppl fishing nearby ... niceüëçüëçüëç‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Took a sunday afternoon stroll along the beach walk to clear my head. You can ride a bike or a scooter or just lay on the grass and enjoy the breeze... Some people might prefer fishing along the shore. Whatever the case its a nice place to relax and unwind

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Changi beach park is at the end of Singapore island, not easy to reach by public transport. The beach area has a lot of people, but not as crowded as East Coast park. It‚Äôs also the best place for aviation fans as you can see plane landing or take off from there (carpark 4 will be the best) there is also a restaurant and bike rental. If need to get food, can walk over to Changi village across the bridge.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: An Ok place for fishing. Somehow quite place. Plane flying over is seen less compared to previous times as flight direction is changed. Take rental bike and stroll on the park connector there. Frequency of washroom is less. Beach is not clean. Best time to visit is at evening.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: A very nice place to hang out also very windy. Nice beaches and further of all very clean environment.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Nature will hug you in this place. Wonderful

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: For drivers, park at car park 1 which is nearer to the stone bridge. A good place for dinner at Changi village after evening stroll at the beach. However, car park 2 and 3 are also very near by. There are open air car parks, road is quite flat towards the beach. Changi point  jetty is near by, the scenary is much nicer than east coast with many boats around

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Very nice and serence beach. Undisturbed during weekday time. Nearest drink stall / vending machine is in vhangi Beach island area. If u are in broadwalk area. Do bring along an towel n water. It's an long 15-20 mins walk.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Windy, peaceful, nice place to chill.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: A beautiful place to unwind. Rest relax and briskwalk enjoying the sea breeze and watch low flying aircraft. The food prices at the hawker centre is reasonable. You can even catch ferry to Tekong and a newly open restaurant off changi point and pulau Ubin Smith Marine to enjoy catching live fish and cook it as you wish while watching the sunset and enjoy your dinner.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: For some fresh air and sea breeze, with children playing by the beach, during weekends or school holidays, parking spaces takes longer time to find for those driving own vehicle. For those who want to avoid the aftn sun, they can come in late evening. Carpark A is for those who did not bring food/drinks as its near to the Changi Village food centre by walking.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: nice place to cycle and stroll around.. plenty of bbq pits which you can book.. changi village food centre is nearby too..

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Changi Beach is a bit silent beach, Have many BBQs here. Good thing that public toilet is available near to Car Park2, which make people comfort if you played on beach or you drinks and looking for washroom.
Bus stop just 2mins walk, which also one of the good point.
One thing which I didn't liked was beach cleanliness, Changi Beach is not recommended for playing with water and take bath. Rocks are there and bit dirty.
For real feel of beach and seashore, ECP is highly recommend. Have attached few photos which tell you about rocks and less crowd. Recommend if you are planning for party at seashore..

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: A sandy beach with long walk spot with many peoples fishing in the sea. Really nice view that to be so close in sea shore.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
It's lovely here, right next to the Changi Village hawker centre and Changi ferry terminal.

In the morning it is incredibly peaceful and beautiful, you will see the occasional jogger or fisherman (or maybe a lone kit) passing by. Otherwise you can really tune out and wind down here to connect with the world and escape the hustle and bustle of the city centre

As a rite of passage when visiting Singapore, you definitely should make a day trip and come to watch the sunrise on the beach and then take a ferry to Pulau Ubin.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: This is a gem of world collided. On a week day before 11am sitting in the shade watching the many ships at anchor in the Singapore Strait can be an education in itself. And there are the jets in final approach to Changi airport. Paddling or even swimming in the luke warm sea with sand between your toes yet another unexpected experience. Nature and the modern world in a sort of harmony.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Great place to hang out with family and kids, surprisingly the sand is quite white and smooth.. A must see if those who reside in east.. Nice and clean with too many eatery option just in the front. The place is very near to the changi ferry terminal for going to pulaubin. This place also has children play area which is good.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Our place to go for our family hand out.  Cycling, people watching, chillax. Changi Beach Park is a huge beach connecting to East Coast Beach. Best place for plane watching as it's nearer to the airport.  Can't remember which car park, you will be able to see people Kite Surfings. Go explore !

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Located in Singapore, a 20-minute walk from Changi Point Jetty Ferry Terminal, Changi Beach Club Resort has accommodations with a shared lounge, free private parking and a private beach area. Around 8 km from Singapore EXPO Convention & Exhibition Center, the property is also 8 km away from Changi City Point and offers free WiFi. The resort has family rooms.

An Asian breakfast is available each morning at the resort.

Singapore Sports Hub is 17.7 km from Changi Beach Club Resort, while Mustafa Center is 20.9 km from the property.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Lovely place to visit anytime of the day... It has its own corners and places and beautiful nature to indulge in.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Pretty beach park to have picnic or barbeque with friends and family. Changi Village Hawker Center is also nearby to get delicious food.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Looking out across the Singapore strait towards Pulao Ubin, it's a great place to relax, enjoy the sand, maybe do a little fishing and have a bbq with the family..  Great Cycling pit-stop too before heading back to the east-coast park..

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Nice quiet beach, especially early mornings. Great to watch the sunrise, passing ships, and planes flying overhead. There is a stretch of beach which is great for swimming.

Don't forget also the history of Changi beach, which was at the forefront of the Japanese invasion during WWII.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Nostalgic Place which has been Upgraded
Used to go to this beach when it was all undeveloped- no running tracks, carpark or playground.

Now that it has all those, the charm of the wild is lost but you get some convenience.

Beach still looks inviting and it was wonderful weather today - sunny but wind kept it cool.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Part of the beaches are closed due the covid19. Still we were here for few hours. Upset and dissapointed even going out with the folks and one child.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Open and airy, plenty of space to walk/ cycle/ pinic. A bit simple though and amenities are limited compared to East Coast Park. Slightly far for plane spotting.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Lovely Place to play with the kids. Somewhat crowded on the weekends but still has plenty of space at the beach

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
A very quiet beach where you can simply have a sit at the bench or have a picnic just on the grass patch to see the sunset or sunrise.

There is a bar available in the park if you like to chill out. Kids can enjoy themselves at the playgrounds provided. A good place for walk and cycling.

Please note that the beaches may be infected with sandfly and mosquitoes. So, please protect yourself with insect repellent and antiseptic cream.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Beautiful beach.. but I wish ppl would be responsible and pick up their litter..

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Love the long jogging and walking stretch....enjoyed the dining at the restaurant Sea Grill too....

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Nice seaside park, beautiful view of the sea and lots of benches to sit around. Even has a cafe bistro for meals with nice ambience. Lots of cats sitting around too. Nice place for a stroll and watch the sunrise or sunset. Paved walkways make walking or cycling convenient

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
I agree with others that an early morning visit is really a great time to watch the day unfold over the sea and be carried to the shore on platinum tinted waves that burst into gold as they unfurl along the pale sandy beach. In addition, there are paved paths for easy cycling or jogging, plus picnic and bbq areas. Many shade trees or fun sun, your choice.
I would recommend water shoes for wading. I would not swim here, though, as this is a major shipping thoroughfare and oily seas are sometimes an issue. Consider bug repellent as mosquitoes or sand flies are occasionally bothersome.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: Great place to chill and unwind. Good to spot planes as well! Recommended to visit and parking js easy

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: A nice and great cost area for walk, cycling and riding. Weather was just nice and there is a bicycle rental shop (including those bike with child seats) just beside carpark 1. After exiting the bicycle shop, we cycled to the left, then u-turn back towards right side all the way and returned in almost 1hr with a few stop-overs for photograph takings.

name: Changi Beach Park

Quiet and serene, except for occasional planes passing overhead, as the beach is located beside the path of planes approaching Changi Airport.

Facing Pulau Ubin and Tekong Island, this beach is rich in history. It is one of the places where British allied forces tried to repel Japanese forces during World War II.

On this beach, the sook ching massacre or purification killings were done by the Japanese military on Chinese civilians suspected of being enemies.

Now, it is a place of recreation where people spend time with their families and friends.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text: A laid back coastal park with many F&B outlets within a stone's throw.  One can expect families in droves having picnics or gathering during the typical sunny weekends.  There is a caf√© (The Seagrill)  that served food and drinks with a nice view.  Beer and alcohol are available too for those who love to chill by the beach while feeling tipsy.  Those with bicycles, skates or power devices can venture to the nearby Changi Bay Point which is picturesque and a little like 'Jeju' as some might say.  Changi Beach Park has also been a place where couples and families with kids watch planes land and takeoff before the pandemic hit.  Pretty sure the density of planes would resume very soon.  A laid back and romantic place in the evenings for couples and those looking for a place to romance their prospective partners.

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
This is a small beach at the eastern tip of Singapore. ( By small , I mean comparing it to its neighbour , East Coast Park beach .)

But ,being smaller it's quieter ( if you know when to go ) .

It's also the only beach where you can see airline planes flying into Changi Airport at close range ( Close enough to see the airline markings ) It used to be 1 flight every 5 minutes , before Covid . Nowadays , it's  15 or 20 minutes per flight. ).

You can also see neighbouring islands not far away from the beach and most importantly, you can see real sea view . Unlike it's neighbour Marine Parade beach ,where you see all sorts of ships on the sea , coming into the Singapore port , blocking the sea view. ( Hence , the name Marine Parade . It's a parade place for ships )

Changi beach is a good place to be.

It may seem like an ordinary beach. But I love this place. There are many good things about this one - you should start from the right most point, where you can see the aircrafts passing over your head for landing, you will feel like jumping to touch them each time üôÇ (pre-covid Ofcourse, and don‚Äôt sigh, there will definitely be a post-covid period too).
As you walk toward the left you will see families having picnics, there are many bar-be-que pits, kids play area, people with their hooks in the water waiting for a catch. beside the crows, mynahs and pigeons you can easily spot cockatoos, hornbills and parakeets. I particularly like to climb up those wonderful trees,as it takes me back to my childhood. The left most point in the park, an oval shape beach, is my favorite part, it‚Äôs a good point to spot otters too. It is also the area from where you can catch a ferry to the wetlands in pulau-ubin just by crossing a foot over bridge. Please go and enjoy !!!

name: Changi Beach Park
review_text:
Great place to relax. Enjoy the warm breezes and watch the planes approaching to land at Changi Airport. Planes approach at an average of one every 2-3 minutes.

You can also watch the sunrise, swim in the warm waters or just walk along the sandy beach. Where we were (Carpark 1), there are some shelters, benches, a free public toilet with showering facilities, a children's playground and a store selling hit and cold beverages, snacks and renting out bicycles. For more choices and cheaper food and drinks, just cross a small footbridge to get to the Changi Village Food Centre where some stalls are open 24/7.

Some observations to note. The shelters seem to be "permanently" occupied by some people though. You can even see their laundry hanging on the trees and bags of their possessions scattered throughout the shelters.
